bib.title: Polarization transfer measurements for the (d,pX) reaction at E(d)=65 MeV and the reaction mechanism for the protons in the continuum

free_txt: Data of Fig.9, Fig.10 anf Fig.11 from the
reference are compiled, and most BIB
Solid angle of the DUMAS/MUSASHI system were 0.86
+-0.43 msr for measurements at 7.0 degrees and 2.15
Pure vector polarized beam (up and down) in the ideal
case was used. The tensor polarization remained less
than 4% during the experiment. The effect of the
remaining tensor component on the evaluation of the
vector beam polarization and the other observables was
estimated to be less than one percent. The beam
polarization was around 82% of the ideal value
